# **08  Competitive response plan**

If a well-funded competitor enters the meal decision category during our MVP phase, this is the response playbook.

| **Scenario** | **Likelihood** | **Response** |
| --- | --- | --- |
| **Zomato/Swiggy adds ****'****what to eat****'**** feature** | Medium | Accelerate. Their feature will be restaurant-centric, not home-cooking-centric. Double down on household intelligence and regional depth — neither can be replicated in months. |
| **HealthifyMe pivots to proactive meal planning** | Medium | Their positioning (health goals, premium pricing ₹999+/month) is different. We own the everyday household utility space. Continue building the RE moat. |
| **New funded startup enters meal decision space** | Low | Copy cannot replicate the dish genome database (months of research) or the 41-persona cohort matrix. Execute faster. Referral and household data are compounding moats. |
| **Global meal kit player enters India** | Very low | Meal kits are a different product (ingredient delivery + recipe). Foofoo is the decision layer. Complementary, not competing. |

